    "Regime Switch (trend/vol router)": {
      "rule": "Trend rules earn in sustained moves; mean reversion earns in chop. Route between them with the best-documented state variables: the 200-day trend filter (Faber 2007, JWM) and realized-volatility clustering (Engle 1982; Schwert 1989). Risk-on (SPY above its 200d MA and 20d vol under 30% annualized) holds 1/2 DualMomentum + 1/2 Donchian; risk-off holds MeanReversion, which in stress is naturally mostly cash. All three sub-rules already have measured records in this tournament \u2014 this adds only the routing layer. Null hypothesis: the equal-weight ensemble of the same three rules; if switching cannot beat that forward, it is noise.",
